H. C. JONES, Collector of Internal Revenue for the District of Oklahoma, and H. C. Jones, an Individual, v. Kent B. HAYES, Executor of the Estate of Samuel W. Hayes, deceased, and Kent B. Hayes, an Individual. No. 3354. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. June 5, 1946. Charles E. Dierker, U. S. Atty., of Oklahoma City, Okl., for appellant. Richardson, Shartel, Cochran and Pruet, of Oklahoma City, Okla., for appellee.

Before PHILLIPS, Circuit Judge, and SYMES, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal docketed and dismissed pursuant to stipulation.
